timing_report_...ormatting_mode(25.10)  timing_report_...ormatting_mode(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_retime_formatting_mode

Syntax
       timing_report_retime_formatting_mode

       {manual | retime_compare | retime_replace}

       Default: manual

       Controls retiming fields to be displayed in the timing report.

       You  can  set  one  of  the  following  options to change the reporting
       columns:

              * manual: Does not change the report_timing format.

              * retime_compare: If GBA columns are present in the report  for-
                mat,  then the corresponding retime options are added.  If PBA
                columns are already present, then there is no  change  in  the
                format.

              * retime_replace:  If GBA columns are present in the report for-
                mat, then the GBA columns are replaced  by  the  corresponding
                PBA  columns.  If  PBA columns are already in the report, then
                there is no change in the format.

       Note: The report format is also controlled  through  the  report_timing
       -retime_format  parameter. The report_timing command setting has prece-
       dence over this global variable.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

